{"word":"H5874 - עֵין־דֹּאר - ʻÊyn-Dôʼr - ane-dore' - En-dor","slug":"H5874","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עֵין־דֹּאר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻÊyn-Dôʼr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ane-dore'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>En-dor"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>עין־דּר עין דּור עין־דּאר</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>‛êyn-d'ôr ‛êyn dôr ‛êyn-dôr</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>ane-dore'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> En-dor = \"fountain of Dor\" <ol><li>a place in the territory of Issachar yet possessed by Manasseh; located 4 miles (6.5 kilometers) north of Tabor<ol type='a'><li>place of residence of the spiritist consulted by king Saul</li></ol></li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H5869\">H5869</a> and <a href=\"#/H1755\">H1755</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Location "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4599\">H4599</a>, <a href=\"#/H5770\">H5770</a>, <a href=\"#/H5869\">H5869</a>, <a href=\"#/H5871\">H5871</a>, <a href=\"#/H5872\">H5872</a>, <a href=\"#/H5873\">H5873</a>, <a href=\"#/H5875\">H5875</a>, <a href=\"#/H5876\">H5876</a>, <a href=\"#/H5877\">H5877</a>, <a href=\"#/H5879\">H5879</a>, <a href=\"#/H5880\">H5880</a>, <a href=\"#/H5881\">H5881</a>, <a href=\"#/H5882\">H5882</a>, <a href=\"#/H5883\">H5883</a>, <a href=\"#/H5884\">H5884</a>, <a href=\"#/H5885\">H5885</a>, <a href=\"#/H5886\">H5886</a>, <a href=\"#/H6044\">H6044</a>, <a href=\"#/H6046\">H6046</a>"}]}